From aa72d37f754f8c959e90d9044231280cba0102e0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Peipei Wang <pewang@confluent.io>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 15:12:44 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] Add per-query HNSW trace instrumentation controlled by
 hnsw.trace GUC

Instruments pgvector's HNSW index scan to emit detailed per-query
metrics as JSON via elog(INFO) when SET hnsw.trace = on. Tracks:
distance_compute_count, visited_nodes, heap_fetch_count,
index element/neighbor page loads, page runs, distinct pages,
and end-to-end latency. Non-scan paths (build, insert, vacuum)
pass NULL trace and are unaffected.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
